de.iabg.mode
Class ModeCorrelationTableModel

java.lang.Object
  javax.swing.table.AbstractTableModel
      de.iabg.mode.ModeCorrelationTableModel
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, javax.swing.table.TableModel
public class ModeCorrelationTableModel
extends javax.swing.table.AbstractTableModel
implements javax.swing.table.TableModel

This implementation of a TableModel provides a table representation of a ModeCorrelationMatrix. This class bridges the connection between a ModeCorrelationMatrix and a ModeCorrelationModel by simply adding a table representation. Therefore, some of the methods of this class wrap those in ModeCorrelationMatrix, while other methods are wrapped in ModeCorrelationModel. Most of the descriptions of the methods in this class can be found by refering to the API of either of those two classes. The remaining methods generally implement or override those specified in TableModel. Refer to the API or tutorial for using Table Models for more details. This TableModel provides nine columns to represent a ModeCorrelationMatrix: The first is called Selected or On, which selects the corresponding mode connection. Selecting or deselecting this option can allow specified mode connections to be output to a file. The second column is called Mode 1 or First Mode, which displays the identifier of the First Mode. The third column is called Mode Weighting or WFM, which displays the correlation weighting factor of the corresponding mode connection. This value can be edited by the user. The fourth column is called Freq 1 or First Frequency, which displays the frequency of the First Mode. The fifth column is called Frequency Weighting or WFF, which displays the frequency weighting factor of the corresponding mode connection. The sixth column is called Mode 2 or Last Mode, which displays the identifier of the connected Last Mode. The default value for this comes from the preferred connection, however, the user may change this to any other mode. The seventh column is called Freq 2 or Last Frequency, which displays the frequency of the Last Mode. This value is automatically updated when the user changes the Last Mode. The eighth column is called Correlation or simply Value, which displays the corresponding correlation value between the selected First Mode and Last Mode. This value is automatically updated when the user changes the Last Mode. The ninth column is called Frequency Difference or dFreq, which displays the frequency difference between the selected First Mode and Last Mode. This value is automatically updated when the user changes the Last Mode. The rows of this table reflect the total number of mode connections that are currently stored.
